  "text": "The Kubernetes informer cache event handler chain traces from API server watch events to informer cache updates through the following pipeline:\n\n## 1. ListWatch (tools/cache/listwatch.go)\nThe `ListWatch` struct implements the `ListerWatcher` interface, providing two key methods:\n- `List()`: Performs an initial list of all objects from the API server\n- `Watch()`: Establishes a watch stream to receive events as objects change\n\n## 2. Reflector (tools/cache/reflector.go)\nThe `Reflector` struct orchestrates the watch and cache update process:\n- `Run()`: Main loop that initiates `ListAndWatch()`\n- `ListAndWatch()`: Performs initial list and establishes watch connection\n- `watchWithResync()`: Wraps the watch with periodic resync capability\n- `watch()`: Main watch loop that calls `handleAnyWatch()`\n- `handleAnyWatch()`: Processes watch events from the API server stream (Added/Modified/Deleted events) and calls store methods\n\nThe Reflector receives events from the API server's watch stream and immediately writes them to the store (DeltaFIFO) by calling `store.Add()`, `store.Update()`, or `store.Delete()`.\n\n## 3. DeltaFIFO Queue (tools/cache/delta_fifo.go)\nThe `DeltaFIFO` struct is a producer-consumer queue that:\n- Accumulates deltas (changes) for each object\n- The `Reflector` adds events to this queue (Add/Update/Delete operations)\n- The `Pop()` method is called by the controller to retrieve accumulated deltas\n\n## 4. Store (tools/cache/store.go) and ThreadSafeStore (tools/cache/thread_safe_store.go)\nThe `Store` interface defines Add/Update/Delete/List operations.\n- The `cache` struct implements Store with a `ThreadSafeStore` backing\n- Provides thread-safe storage for objects with indexing support\n\n## 5. Controller (tools/cache/controller.go)\nThe `controller` struct connects the Reflector to the informer:\n- `Run()`: Starts both the Reflector and a processing loop\n- `processLoop()`: Continuously pops items from the DeltaFIFO queue\n- The popped items are deltas that are then passed to `processDeltas()`\n- `processDeltas()`: Iterates through each delta and calls handler methods:\n  - For Sync/Replaced/Added/Updated deltas: calls handler `OnAdd()` or `OnUpdate()`\n  - For Deleted deltas: calls handler `OnDelete()`\n\nThe handler here is the `sharedIndexInformer` instance.\n\n## 6. SharedIndexInformer (tools/cache/shared_informer.go)\nThe `sharedIndexInformer` struct implements both the informer interface and the `ResourceEventHandler` interface:\n- `HandleDeltas()`: Entry point from the controller that receives deltas and calls processDeltas\n- `OnAdd()`, `OnUpdate()`, `OnDelete()`: Called by processDeltas to handle specific delta types\n- These methods update the local indexer/cache and then call `sharedProcessor.distribute()` to notify listeners\n\n## 7. SharedProcessor and ProcessorListener (tools/cache/shared_informer.go)\nThe `sharedProcessor` manages event distribution:\n- `distribute()`: Takes a notification and sends it to all registered listeners\n- For each registered `processorListener`, calls `listener.add(notification)`\n\nThe `processorListener` relays notifications to individual registered event handlers:\n- `add()`: Receives notifications and puts them in the pending queue\n- `pop()`: Runs in a separate goroutine and pumps notifications from the pending queue to the handler queue\n- `run()`: Runs in a separate goroutine and calls the actual handler methods (OnAdd/OnUpdate/OnDelete) for each notification\n\n## Event Flow Summary\nAPI Server Watch Stream → Reflector.handleAnyWatch() → DeltaFIFO (store.Add/Update/Delete) → Controller.processLoop() → processDeltas() → sharedIndexInformer.OnAdd/OnUpdate/OnDelete() → sharedProcessor.distribute() → processorListener.add() → processorListener.pop() → processorListener.run() → Registered ResourceEventHandler callbacks\n\nThis architecture ensures that watch events from the API server are eventually delivered to all registered event handlers in a thread-safe manner, with the local cache being updated in the process."
